  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Slice the <strong>green chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely</p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Peel and finely chop (or grate)</span> the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop<span class=\"text-highlight\"> (or grate) t</span>he <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-sesame-noodles/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rip the leaves off the<strong> spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up <span class=\"text-highlight\">and</span> slice into thin strips</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-sesame-noodles/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork mince</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until browned and very crispy, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>\n<p>Once crispy, transfer the <strong>crispy pork</strong> to a plate and set aside</p>\n<p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-sesame-noodles/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>wholewheat noodles</strong> to a pot and cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong> until fully submerged</p>\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p>\n<p>Once tender, drain the <strong>noodles</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: drizzle over a little vegetable oil to stop the noodles from sticking <span class=\"text-highlight\">together</span></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-sesame-noodles/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced spring greens </strong>with a <span class=\"text-highlight\">pinch of</span><strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until wilted </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-sesame-noodles/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>tahini</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Sriracha hot chilli sauce</strong></span>,<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(Can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and<span class=\"text-highlight\"> </span><strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">Chinese rice</span> wine</strong> with 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [80ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> spicy sesame sauce</strong></p>\n<p>Bash the<strong> peanuts</strong> with a <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>rolling pin</strong></span> until roughly crushed (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-sesame-noodles/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained noodles</strong>, <strong>crispy pork</strong> and <strong>spicy sesame sauce</strong> to the pan with the <strong>wilted spring greens</strong> and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>spicy pork &amp; sesame noodles</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: add a splash more <span class=\"text-highlight\">starchy noodle water</span> if the sauce is looking a little <span class=\"text-highlight\">dry</span></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-pork-sesame-noodles/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy pork &amp; sesame noodles </strong></p>\n<p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced green chillies</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>black</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong>, <strong>crushed peanuts</strong> and <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>fried</strong></span><strong> onions</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
